lenders.occupational_info:
Raised on the South side of Milwaukee, WI, eldest child of four. My mom did the best she could do as a single mother. We didn’t have everything we wanted but we sure had everything we needed . What we did have, was a lot of love & a lot faith. Being the oldest child I always had more responsibilities then my siblings, I grew up faster because I had to help take care of my siblings. My mom has always pushed me to be better than she was, career wise .My mother has always been my motivation in life, she expected, no demanded me to be the best that I could be.
My mom was a hair stylist when I was younger & I just found it intriguing. At 16 I started styling my own hair, my mom & friend’s hair for fun & small fees. My mom had high hopes on me graduating from high school & going right on to a four year college.  But to her surprise, styling hair turned into something that I loved. The following year when I graduated from South Division High School, I enrolled in the cosmetology program at Milwaukee Area Technical College. Two years later I graduated & I started an apprenticeship at a salon at 19! I have now been in the hair industry for over 12 years!
 In 2011 I decided I wanted to open my own salon after working in a few different salons over the years. I saved all of my money, used all of my earnings to lease a space & buy all of my equipment. After 2 years in my 1st space, I’d learned most of the pros & cons, what I wanted as far as my business & more importantly what I didn’t want. I found out that it took hard work & patience to be a business owner. So I relocated to a smaller space, where my overhead was less, in a shopping center where I gained more clientele.
 February of 2014, my newest addition to my brand was cosmetics. & it’s called Dolled. My mom was the founder of Dolled. Cosmetics have always been a love & interest of my moms! Dolled is our brand, it’s my lifestyle & legacy. Dolled is a brand created by women for women! Dolled is dedicated to empowering & inspiring women!
 In March, my mom passed away, , causing me to refocus & rethink my career in its entirety & I realized that while I have the chance in life I want to be great,. I want my business & my brand to be great! So I decided to relocate & upgrade my salon so I can have space for my #dolled products. Dolled is really my passion, it fills me with so much life & energy. My new salon space will be named Dolled Headquarters 
 I love my job because I get to make every person that sits in my chair feel great about themselves. I love meeting new people & helping them reach their beauty goals. I am passionate in my profession & truly feel  blessed to be in a career that  I love.#Dolled #DolledbyQui 
Follow my business page on Instagram @ dolled_inc
